Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}. When boiling, add the @Rigatoni Pasta{180%grams} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While the pasta cooks, halve the @Bell Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 1cm chunks. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a garlic press). Drain the @Sweetcorn{160%grams} in a #sieve{}. Drain the @Mozzarella{1%ball} and squeeze out as much liquid as you can. Pat dry with #kitchen paper{}, then tear into small pieces. Grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{30%grams}.

Preheat the #grill{} to high. Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Once hot, add the @Diced British Chicken Breast{260%grams}, pepper chunks and corn. Stir-fry until golden, ~{5-6%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Lower the heat to medium and add the garlic and @Harissa Paste{50%grams} (add less if you'd prefer things milder). Stir-fry for ~{1%minute} more.

Stir in the @Tomato Puree{30%grams}, @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%grams}, @Creme Fraiche{75%grams}, @Sugar{1%tsp for the Sauce} and @Water{150%milliliter} for the sauce.

Bring the sauce to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

When ready, combine the cooked pasta and sauce (in whichever pan is biggest). Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick, then transfer to an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}. Scatter over the mozzarella and Cheddar.

Pop the dish under the grill and cook until the cheese is bubbling and golden, ~{7-8%minutes}.

When ready, share the harissa pasta bake between your #bowls{}. Enjoy!